?ce/6181?sbc/?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>|| Tavern social house \n|-\n| [[File:Brooker Midd.jpg|200px]]||Brooker House||1997<ref>{{cite web |title=Brooker House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61379?ce/6181?sbc/?s/president?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>|| Outdoor interest house and home to the school's Mountain Club\n|-\n| ||Chinese House|| || \n|-\n| [[File:French house Midd.jpg|200px]]||French House|| || \n|-\n| ||Hadley House and Barn|| || Used to host college guests<ref>{{cite web |title=Hadley House and Barn |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61416?s/hadley?ct/6208,6211,6219,6218,6217,6209,6215,6214,6213,6747,6174,6176,6181,6180,6178,6177,6182,6183,6184,2378,6185,6186 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Middlebury campus 15.jpg|200px]]||Hebrew House|| || \n|-\n| ||Homer Harris House|| || \n|-\n| || Homestead House|| || \n|-\n| ||InSite Solar Decathlon House||2013<ref>{{cite web |title=InSite Solar Decathlon House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/111166?ce/6181?sbc/?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> || Middlebury's second house built for the Solar Decathlon; LEED Platinum certified<ref>{{cite web |title=InSite |url=https://www.usgbc.org/projects/insite-0?view=overview |website=U.S. Green Building Council |accessdate=25 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Japanese house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Japanese House|| || \n|-\n| ||Jewett House|| || Wellness House\n|-\n| [[File:Italian house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Longwell House|| || Italian house\n|-\n| [[File:German house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Max Kade Center for German Studies at the Deanery|| || German house||\n|-\n| ||McKiney House|| || \n|-\n| [[File:Meeker House.jpg|200px]]||Meeker House|| || Dormitory\n|-\n| ||Munford House|| || Dormitory\n|-\n| [[File:PALANA Midd.jpg|200px]]||PALANA House|| || PALANA ([[Pan-African]], [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Latino]], [[Asian Americans|Asian]], and [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]]) is the Intercultural Academic Interest House for students interested in diversity and intercultural issues\n|-\n| ||Palmer House||1997<ref>{{cite web |title=Palmer House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61480?ce/6181?sbc/?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>|| \n|-\n| [[File:Portuguese house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Portuguese House|| || \n|-\n| [[File:Prescott house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Prescott House||1997<ref>{{cite web |title=Prescott House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61487?ce/6181?sbc/?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> || Chromatic social house, formerly home to [[Alpha Delta Phi]] fraternity/social house until its suspension in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tudor |first1=Thilan |title=Prescott to be Offered as Superblock |url=https://middleburycampus.com/24431/news/prescott-to-be-offered-as-superblock/ |accessdate=2 October 2018 |work=The Middlebury Campus |date=June 18, 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Middlebury_campus_10.jpg|200px]]||Ross Tower|| || Dormitory. Ross Tower is on the left of the image, and Milliken Hall is on the right. \n|-\n| [[File:Arabic house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Sperry House|| || Arabic house\n|-\n| [[File:The Mill Midd.jpg|200px]]||The Mill || || Social house\n|-\n| 