udent center that works to promote a welcoming and inclusive environment for minority and first-generation students<ref name=AFC />||\n|-\n| [[File:Chellis house.jpg|200px]]||Chellis House || || Home to the [[gender studies]] department and the Women's and Gender Studies Resource Center\n|-\n| [[File:Farrell house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Farrell House || || Faculty offices, used by the economics department as of 2019\n|-\n| [[File:Hesselgrave House.jpg|200px]]||Hesselgrave House|| || Faculty offices\n|-\n| [[File:Kitchel House Midd 1.jpg|200px]]||Kitchel House ||1867<ref name=Kitchel>{{cite web |title=Kitchel House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61437?ce/6174?sbc/ |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>|| Home to Middlebury's Office of Communications and Marketing, as well as the offices for ''Middlebury Magazine''<ref name=Kitchel />\n|-\n| ||Marble Works Offices || || Houses finance, human resources, and business services departments in a building off the campus itself\n|-\n| ||Nichols House || || \n|-\n| ||Old Court House || || In the [[Middlebury, Vermont|town of Middlebury]], off the campus itself\n|-\n| ||President's House|| || \n|-\n| [[File:PubSafe Midd.jpg|200px]]||Public Safety || || \n|-\n| ||Center for Community Engagement || || \n|-\n| [[File:Wonnacott Commons house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Wonnacott Commons House || || \n|-\n| [[File:Middlebury campus 3.jpg|200px]]||107 Shannon Street || || Senior housing (house behind the church)\n|-\n| ||220 College Street || || \n|-\n| [[File:248 College street.jpg|200px]]||248 College Street || || Senior housing \n|-\n| [[File:23 Adirondack view Midd.jpg|200px]]||23 Adirondack View || || Events staff offices\n|-\n| [[File:33 Adirondack view.jpg|200px]]||33 Adirondack View || || \n|-\n| ||48 South Street|| || A dormitory, formerly home to the [[Kappa Delta Rho]] fraternity/social house before it was shut down in 2015 due to a [[hazing]] violation<ref>{{cite news |last1=Flaherty |first1=Joe |title=Hazing Violation Suspends KDR |url=https://middleburycampus.com/30966/news/hazing-violation-suspends-kdr/ |accessdate=2 October 2018 |work=The Middlebury Campus |date=April 8, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ||637 College Street|| || Russian house\n|-\n| [[File:Queer Studies House Midd.jpg|200px]]||70 Hillcrest Road|| || Home to the Queer Studies House (QSH, pronounced \"kwish\"), an academic interest house for students interested in [[queer studies]], since 2008<ref>{{cite web |title=About the QSH |url=http://sites.middlebury.edu/queerstudieshouse/ |website=The Queer Studies House}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:99 Adirondack view.jpg|200px]]||99 Adirondack View|| || \n|-\n| [[File:Xenia Midd front.jpg|200px]]||Bowker House|| || Xenia social house\n|-\n| [[File:Tavern Midd.jpg|200px]]||Brackett House||1997<ref>{{cite web |title=Brackett House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61378?ce/6181?sbc/?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>|| Tavern social house \n|-\n| [[File:Brooker Midd.jpg|200px]]||Brooker House||1997<ref>{{cite web |title=Brooker House |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61379?ce/6181?sbc/?s/president?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>|| Outdoor interest house and home to the school's Mountain Club\n|-\n| ||Chinese House|| || \n|-\n| [[File:French house Midd.jpg|200px]]||French House|| || \n|-\n| ||Hadley House and Barn|| || Used to host college guests<ref>{{cite web |title=Hadley House and Barn |url=https://map.middlebury.edu/?id=229#!m/61416?s/hadley?ct/6208,6211,6219,6218,6217,6209,6215,6214,6213,6747,6174,6176,6181,6180,6178,6177,6182,6183,6184,2378,6185,6186 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |acces