ury.edu/?id=229#!m/61487?ce/6181?sbc/?ct/6228,6227,6226,6186,6185,6184,6183,6182,6181,6180,6178,6177,6176,6174,2378,0 |website=Middlebury Interactive Map |publisher=Middlebury College |accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> || Chromatic social house, formerly home to [[Alpha Delta Phi]] fraternity/social house until its suspension in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tudor |first1=Thilan |title=Prescott to be Offered as Superblock |url=https://middleburycampus.com/24431/news/prescott-to-be-offered-as-superblock/ |accessdate=2 October 2018 |work=The Middlebury Campus |date=June 18, 2006}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Middlebury_campus_10.jpg|200px]]||Ross Tower|| || Dormitory. Ross Tower is on the left of the image, and Milliken Hall is on the right. \n|-\n| [[File:Arabic house Midd.jpg|200px]]||Sperry House|| || Arabic house\n|-\n| [[File:The Mill Midd.jpg|200px]]||The Mill || || Social house\n|-\n| [[File:Turner Midd.jpg|200px]]||Turner House|| || Senior housing\n|-\n| ||Weybridge House|| || [[Food studies]] special interest house\n|-\n| ||David W. Ginevan Recycling Center|| || \n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{commons category|Buildings of Middlebury College}}\n*[[Middlebury College]]\n*[[Middlebury, Vermont]]\n*[[Middlebury College Snow Bowl]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.middlebury.edu Official website]\n* [http://www.middlebury.edu/about/campus/campusmap Middlebury College campus maps]\n\n[[Category:Middlebury College| ]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Vermont]]\n[[Category:Lists of university and college buildings in the United States|Middlebury College]]\n[[Category:Liberal arts colleges]]\n[[Category:Education in Addison County, Vermont]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Addison County, Vermont]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Addison County, Vermont]]\n[[Category:Vermont culture]]\n", "name_user": "R'n'B", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toLatino(link changed toHispanic and Latino Americans) us