{"title_page": "Almetyevsk", "text_new": "{{Infobox Russian city\n|en_name=Almetyevsk\n|ru_name=\u0410\u043b\u044c\u043c\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\n|loc_name1=\u04d8\u043b\u043c\u04d9\u0442\n|loc_lang1=Tatar\n|image_skyline=Almetyevsk.jpg\n|image_caption=Almetyevsk Youth Center\n|coordinates = {{coord|54|54|N|52|18|E|display=inline,title}}\n|map_label_position=top\n|image_coa=\n|coa_caption=\n|image_flag=Coat of Arms of Almetievsk (Tatarstan) (1987).png\n|flag_caption=\n|anthem=\n|anthem_ref=\n|holiday=\n|holiday_ref=\n|federal_subject=[[Republic of Tatarstan]]\n|federal_subject_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|adm_data_as_of=February 2014\n|adm_city_jur=[[city of federal subject significance|city of republic significance]] of Almetyevsk\n|adm_city_jur_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|adm_ctr_of1=city of republic significance of Almetyevsk\n|adm_ctr_of1_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|adm_ctr_of2=[[Almetyevsky District]]\n|adm_ctr_of2_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|inhabloc_cat=City\n|inhabloc_cat_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|inhabloc_type=\n|inhabloc_type_ref=\n|mun_data_as_of=December 2010\n|mun_district_jur=Almetyevsky Municipal District\n|mun_district_jur_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstanAlmetyevskyD_mun\" />\n|urban_settlement_jur=Almetyevsk Urban Settlement\n|urban_settlement_jur_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstanAlmetyevskyD_mun\" />\n|mun_admctr_of1=Almetyevsky Municipal District\n|mun_admctr_of1_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstanAlmetyevskyD_mun\" />\n|mun_admctr_of2=Almetyevsk Urban Settlement\n|mun_admctr_of2_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstanAlmetyevskyD_mun\" />\n|leader_title=\n|leader_title_ref=\n|leader_name=\n|leader_name_ref=\n|representative_body=\n|representative_body_ref=\n|area_of_what=\n|area_as_of=\n|area_km2=\n|area_km2_ref=\n|pop_2010census=146393\n|pop_2010census_rank=117th\n|pop_2010census_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|pop_density=3845\n|pop_density_as_of=\n|pop_density_ref=\n|pop_latest=157673\n|pop_latest_date=2012\n|pop_latest_ref=\n|established_date=1720\n|established_title=First mention\n|established_date_ref=\n|current_cat_date=1953\n|current_cat_date_ref=\n|prev_name1=\n|prev_name1_date=\n|prev_name1_ref=\n|postal_codes=423450-423465\n|postal_codes_ref=\n|dialing_codes=8553\n|dialing_codes_ref=\n|website=\n|website_ref=\n|date=May 2010\n}}\n'''Almetyevsk''' ({{lang-rus|\u0410\u043b\u044c\u043c\u0435\u0301\u0442\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a||\u0250l\u02b2\u02c8m\u02b2et\u02b2j\u026afsk}}; {{lang-tt|\u04d8\u043b\u043c\u04d9\u0442}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|city]] in the [[Republic of Tatarstan]], [[Russia]], located on the left bank of the [[Zay River]] ([[Kama River|Kama]]'s [[tributary]]) {{convert|265|km|sp=us}} southeast of [[Kazan]]. Population: {{ru-census2010|146,393|;}} {{ru-census2002|140,437|;}} {{su-census1989|129,008|;}} 77,000 (1969); 49,000 (1959).\n\n==History==\nAlmetyevsk is one of the youngest cities in the republic. It was founded as an oil-processing settlement and was granted town status in 1953.{{citation needed|date=May 2010}}\n\n==Administrative and municipal status==\nWithin the [[subdivisions of Russia#Administrative divisions|framework of administrative divisions]], Almetyevsk serves as the [[administrative center]] of [[Almetyevsky District]], even though it is not a part of it.<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\">Order #01-02/9</ref> As an administrative division, it is incorporated separately as the '''[[city of federal subject significance|city of republic significance]] of Almetyevsk'''\u2014an administrative unit with the status equal to that of the [[administrative divisions of the Republic of Tatarstan|districts]].<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" /> As a [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|municipal division]], the city of republic significance of Almetyevsk is incorporated within Almetyevsky Municipal District as '''Almetyevsk Urban Settlement'''.<ref name=\"RTatarstanAlmetyevskyD_mun\">Law #9-ZRT</ref>\n\n==Industry==\nAlmetyevsk is an important center of Russia's [[oil industry]]. The [[Druzhba pipeline]] starts in Almetyevsk. [[Pipeline transport|Pipelines]] to [[Nizhny Novgorod]], [[Samara, Russia|Samara]], and [[Subkhankulovo]] also start in this city. The city houses several oil equipment plants producing pipes, pumps and other oil tools.\n\n==Sports==\nMajor sport enterprise in the city is an ice-hockey team \"Neftyanik\" presented in VHL league and sponsored by TatNeft. The team's main records are bronze medalists of Russian Championship Higher League (2002/2003 years ), gold medalists of Russian Championship Higher League (1997-1998 and 1999-2000), silver medalists of VHL 2010/2011 year, 2015/2016 Bratina Cup winners\n\n==References==\n\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|ta|adm|list}}\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|ta|mun|list|almetyevsky}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://almetewsk.ru/ Unofficial website of Almetyevsk] {{in lang|ru}}\n*[http://www.makewebmap.com/city.php?kod=2311089-ru Pictures of Almetyevsk ]\n\n{{Republic of Tatarstan}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2011}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Tatarstan]]\n[[Category:Samara Governorate]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Russian city\n|en_name=Almetyevsk\n|ru_name=\u0410\u043b\u044c\u043c\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\n|loc_name1=\u04d8\u043b\u043c\u04d9\u0442\n|loc_lang1=Tatar\n|image_skyline=Almetyevsk.jpg\n|image_caption=Almetyevsk Youth Center\n|coordinates = {{coord|54|54|N|52|18|E|display=inline,title}}\n|map_label_position=top\n|image_coa=\n|coa_caption=\n|image_flag=Coat of Arms of Almetievsk (Tatarstan) (1987).png\n|flag_caption=\n|anthem=\n|anthem_ref=\n|holiday=\n|holiday_ref=\n|federal_subject=[[Republic of Tatarstan]]\n|federal_subject_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|adm_data_as_of=February 2014\n|adm_city_jur=[[city of federal subject significance|city of republic significance]] of Almetyevsk\n|adm_city_jur_ref=<ref name=\"RTatarstan_adm\" />\n|